getSelection

public Selection getSelection(java.awt.event.MouseEvent e)
Description copied from interface: ObjectSelector
Most object selectors will just use this method as a delegate to ObjectSelector.getSelection(). This method should be overridden if a special selection should be used for right-clicks, drags, etc based on mouse position

setLive

public void setLive(boolean isLive)
The global SelectionManager cannot be made "unlive", since the definition of a "live" SelectionManager is one that is linked to the global selection. Any attempt to make the global selection manager unlive will result in a runtime exception.

Specified by:
